raw 1 new "axis-A-nexus-kick-optimal-external-only-mandate - nexus territory owns axis A (kick optimal model) per user directive 2026-05-01 ('aa axis A 는 nexus 영역.'). Axis A core spec verbatim from user 2026-05-01 directive: 'A. kick 의 최적 작동 (블로킹 0, 자원은 외부자원사용, hexa 작동은 반드시 외부자원이어야한다)'. Three invariants: (1) blocking 0 — caller fires kick and returns immediately, no sync await on the fire API itself; await is OPTIONAL separate API (status() poll / await(handle, timeout_ms) gate); (2) external resources — Mac local CPU / RAM / disk consumption during kick fire MUST approach 0; actual hexa execution body runs on remote host (ubu1 / ubu2 / hetzner / future host pool member) routed via host_pool_canonical pick; (3) hexa execution external strict — Mac local hexa_interp spawn during a kick fire dispatch is BANNED. Every kick that involves a hexa script body MUST route through `hive resource exec <host> --command \"hexa run <script>\"` so the hexa_interp process spawns on remote host, NOT Mac. A-MODULES already-land (mirrored in ~/.hive/state/session_models/modules_registry.hxc axis A section, 25+ entries): kick_main (path /Users/ghost/core/hive/tool/kick_main.hexa, score 8.95) / kick_core (8.95) / kick_io (8.45) / kick_concurrency_lock (active, 9.30) / kick_health_monitor (8.50) / kick_slot_gate (7.95) / kick_lint (8.30) / hive_kick_canonical_lint (8.95) / nexus_kick_canonical_lint (8.55) / ai_cli_autonomous_lint (8.10) / kick_realtime_emit_lint (8.20) / kick_repair_first_lint (8.75) / kick_resolver_bypass_lint (8.30) / stuck_kick_chain_reaper (8.20) / cli_run_entry_guard (path /Users/ghost/core/nexus/cli/run.hexa, 8.05) / kick_dispatch (path /Users/ghost/core/nexus/tool/kick_dispatch.hexa, 9.05) / kick_parallel (8.40) / kick_bench (7.85) / kick_tree (7.05) / nexus_kick_handler (path packages/hive-claude-hook-bus/handlers/nexus_kick.hexa, 9.30) / launchd_queue_drain (path ~/.hive/scripts/kick_queue_drain.sh, 8.30) / hexa_url_handler (path ~/.hx/bin/hexa-url-handler.sh, 8.85) / hexa_url_gate (path /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/gate/hexa_url.hexa, 8.95) / oauth_slot_pre_kick_gate (8.85). 25+ modules ≥ raw 260 modules_per_axis ≥ 3 invariant satisfied. ACTIVE BINDING: kick_concurrency_lock 9.30 (raw 240 v2 r25 lock-system). FAILOVER ORDER: rank=2 nexus_kick_handler 9.30, rank=3 kick_dispatch 9.05. EXTERNAL-RESOURCE PATH SSOT: Every kick body executes through `hive resource exec <host> --command \"hexa run <relative_path> <args>\"` where <host> is picked via host_pool_canonical (own 5 SSOT) from {hetzner, ubu1, ubu2}. Mac local execution is permitted ONLY for the kick fire dispatch act itself (host pick + ssh dispatch decision = sub-100ms overhead, no hexa body), NOT for the hexa body itself. The kick fire act delegates to launchd_queue_drain (path ~/.hive/scripts/kick_queue_drain.sh) which queues the kick as a queue file under ~/.hive/queue/kick_*.json then a launchd-fired drain script reads queue + ssh-dispatches to remote host. Banned patterns surfaced in kick fire path: (a) `KICK_LEGACY_LOCAL=1` env flag — Mac local fallback 영구 폐기 per raw 100 alternative-dispatcher 2026-04-29 directive; (b) direct invocation of `hexa run <script>` on Mac during kick fire (caller-side fork) — bypasses external-resource mandate; (c) blocking `kick await` where the fire API itself waits for completion — caller MUST get a Handle and poll, OR call separate await API; (d) hardcoded host literal in kick fire path (e.g. `ssh ubu2 ...` literal in code) — MUST go through host_pool_canonical pick; (e) hardcoded module path reference (e.g. caller imports `kick_dispatch.hexa` directly bypassing axis-A core invocation surface). Allowed: bootstrap module with status=\"WIP\" + estimate_only=true score during ramp (e.g. distributed-kick-mesh A10 status=cost-3x-resource); raw 91 honest C3 fail-loud when no host available (host_pool returns empty AND no fallback registered) — fail-loud is REQUIRED, NOT silent skip; explicit user override `--local-execute` flag with disambiguation trailer + canonical citation for trace audit. SANCTIONED CHANNELS: (i) `nexus kick <topic>` (canonical CLI surface, raw 99 single-entry) — internally routes through kick_concurrency_lock + host_pool_canonical pick + ssh dispatch; (ii) `hive resource exec <host> --command \"hexa run nexus/cli/run.hexa kick run <topic>\"` (manual escape-hatch via hive resource canonical channel — own 8 cross-host-fix-via-hive-cli-only-mandate compliant); (iii) launchd queue drain via ~/.hive/scripts/kick_queue_drain.sh + ~/Library/LaunchAgents/dev.hexa-lang.kick-drain.plist (1m cadence). MEASUREMENT AXES: mac_local_hexa_fire_count_per_kick = 0 (zero hexa_interp spawn on Mac during kick fire body — measured via host audit row); external_host_dispatch_rate ≥ 0.99 (99%+ of kick fires reach remote host); blocking_detected_count = 0 (no caller observed waiting > 100ms for fire API to return — measured via tool/kick_lint and stuck_kick_chain_reaper audit rows); A-axis active_module_score ≥ 9.0 (current 9.30 ✓); modules_per_axis ≥ 3 (current 25+ ✓). FALSIFIERS: F-NEXUS-RAW1-1: 30d post-registration any kick fire detected to spawn `hexa_interp` on Mac (via host_audit row inspection / lsof on Mac during kick) = retire active module, fallback. F-NEXUS-RAW1-2: 30d post blocking_detected_count > 0 over rolling 30d via kick_lint audit = retire active. F-NEXUS-RAW1-3: 30d post external_host_dispatch_rate < 0.99 = strengthen, retire conservative module. F-NEXUS-RAW1-4: 30d post any new kick fire path code references hardcoded host literal (grep `ssh ubu1\\|ssh ubu2\\|ssh htz` in kick fire path outside host_pool_canonical itself) = directionality violation. F-NEXUS-RAW1-5: 30d post any caller code references `tool/kick_<...>.hexa` path directly bypassing nexus kick canonical CLI surface = pluggable-swap mandate violated. ENFORCEMENT TRIAD per raw 95: (a) tool/kick_lint.hexa already-land for blocking-detect + Mac-local-hexa-spawn detection; tool/nexus_kick_canonical_lint.hexa already-land for canonical-CLI-entry enforcement; tool/host_pool_canonical_lint.hexa for host-literal-ban; (b) raw 197 agent self-replay during kick fire turn rejects hardcoded host literals + Mac local hexa fire patterns; (c) session-start brief-frame load (raw 30 / raw 236) surfaces nexus raw 1 + canonical kick CLI surface for new agent sessions. Five cognitive frameworks (raw 117 5-check ≥3): (i) Unix `nohup` / `disown` non-blocking dispatch pattern (Stevens 1992 APUE — fire and forget); (ii) message queue architecture (POSIX mqueue / RabbitMQ — producer non-blocking with broker absorption); (iii) host pool routing (own 5 SSOT precedent — uniform-spread across {hetzner, ubu1, ubu2}); (iv) raw 260 N-axis META precedent (axis A is the FIRST instantiation per user directive territory carve-out); (v) own 7 R-policy core+module precedent (kick has same shape as resource pick). Five realization channels (raw 117 5-check ≥3): (i) modules_registry.hxc axis A section 25+ entries; (ii) launchd queue drain (~/.hive/scripts/kick_queue_drain.sh + plist); (iii) nexus_kick_handler (claude hook UserPromptSubmit async detached); (iv) nexus kick canonical CLI surface (`nexus kick <topic>`); (v) host_pool_canonical pick. Three counter-examples (raw 117 5-check ≥3): (i) explicit user override `--local-execute` with disambiguation trailer (raw 258 explicit_override carve-out — permitted but logged); (ii) Mac-only diagnostic dry-run that prints what would be dispatched without actually firing (no hexa body executes — out of scope of fire path); (iii) bootstrap host onboarding before host_pool_canonical has any entry (raw 168 minimum-viable scope — single-host genuine constraint). raw 91 honest C3 ≥5: (1) launchd_queue_drain Mac-side kick fire dispatch act itself runs on Mac (sub-100ms overhead — host pick decision + ssh launch); the BAN scope is hexa BODY execution, not the dispatch act; (2) cli_run_entry_guard score 8.05 includes 0.5 blocking penalty for sync entry path — escape-hatch only via `&` background or `hive resource exec` indirection; (3) distributed-kick-mesh A10 estimate score 0.75 status=cost-3x-resource = forward-spec module not yet active; (4) reverse-ssh fallback chain (KICK_VIA_MAC_REVERSE β architecture) is registered as alternative path per raw 100 — disambiguation trailer required when invoked, NOT silent fallback; (5) raw 240 v2 cycle r25 lock-system R/W active module kick_concurrency_lock includes its own selfdog probes — score 9.30 reflects integrated selfdog discipline. enforce tool/kick_lint.hexa. enforce tool/nexus_kick_canonical_lint.hexa. enforce tool/host_pool_canonical_lint.hexa. enforce-layer hive-agent + cli-lint + kick-canonical-self-test. proof ~/.hive/state/session_models/modules_registry.hxc axis A section (25+ entries). proof ~/.hive/state/session_models/active_bindings.hxc binding axis=A (kick_concurrency_lock 9.30 active). proof ~/.hive/state/session_models/axis_A_scores.jsonl (A1-A10+ score ledger). proof ~/.hive/scripts/kick_queue_drain.sh. proof /Users/ghost/core/hive/packages/hive-claude-hook-bus/handlers/nexus_kick.hexa (claude hook handler). spec-form forward-spec. paired-roadmap-id P2026-05-01.nexus.1. deps hive-raw:n-axis-pluggable-core-module-meta-architecture (raw 260). deps hive-raw:axes-B-C-hive-specialization-mandate (raw 261). deps hive-raw:nexus-kick-canonical-cli-mandate (raw 99). deps hive-raw:alternative-dispatcher-clause (raw 100). deps hive-raw:zero-user-touch-automation-mandate (raw 259). deps hive-own:host-pool-deterministic-routing-cli-canonical (own 5). deps hive-own:cross-host-fix-via-hive-cli-only-mandate (own 8). category routing-dispatch + meta-triad. applies-to kick-fire-act + hexa-body-execution + caller-non-blocking-contract. phase fire-time + dispatch-record + bind-promote + 30d-window-audit. severity warn. Distinct from hive raw 260 (N-axis META — nexus raw 1 = axis A SPECIALIZATION instantiation per territory carve-out). Distinct from hive raw 261 (B+C hive specialization — nexus raw 1 = A nexus specialization mirror). Distinct from hive raw 99 (canonical-CLI single-entry runtime dispatch GENERAL — nexus raw 1 = kick-fire-non-blocking + external-resource-strict SPECIALIZATION above raw 99). Distinct from hive raw 100 (alternative-dispatcher fallback — nexus raw 1 = the strengthening that retires KICK_LEGACY_LOCAL=1 Mac fallback path). Distinct from hive own 5 (host-pool routing scope — nexus raw 1 = kick fire body MUST consume host_pool, host_pool itself is own 5 SSOT). User directive verbatim 2026-05-01 (axis A): 'A. kick 의 최적 작동 (블로킹 0, 자원은 외부자원사용, hexa 작동은 반드시 외부자원이어야한다)'. User directive verbatim (territory): 'aa axis A 는 nexus 영역. axis B/C 는 hive 영역.'. raw 117 5-check: genus slug ✓ (axis-A-nexus-kick-optimal-external-only-mandate, 5-genus composite axis-A+nexus+kick-optimal+external-only+mandate per raw 106) + ≥3 cognitive frameworks ✓ (5 declared) + ≥3 realization channels ✓ (5 declared) + ≥3 counter-examples ✓ (3 declared) + ≥5 falsifiers ✓ (F-NEXUS-RAW1-1..5). Cross-repo per raw 47: hive (raw 260 META + raw 261 B+C specialization counterpart), anima (kick-via-harvest consumer), hexa-lang (kick body language runtime), airgenome / n6-architecture (downstream consumers). 30d ramp post-registration. proof-obligations mac_local_hexa_fire_count_per_kick-stable-=0-30d + external_host_dispatch_rate-stable-≥0.99-30d + blocking_detected_count-stable-=0-30d + nexus-raw-1-self-apply-PASS-at-registration (axis A bindings + 25+ modules enumerable). omega-stop fixpoint-convergence. classifier-version raw_240_v2.6_800_800. Genus slug per raw 106. Cross-repo per raw 47."
